<title type="html"><![CDATA[APU frame counter speed on Dendy?]]></title>

<content type="html" xml:base="http://forums.nesdev.com/viewtopic.php?t=9011&amp;p=96314#p96314"><![CDATA[
I'm referring to CPU cycles per APU frame counter tick, not the rate of the frame counter in Hz.<br /><br />I still don't have solid tested numbers for this (someone needs to run Blargg's APU Frame IRQ test on a Dendy to see if it exactly matches NTSC), but I see that it's running at approximately NTSC speed (~7456 cycles per tick) instead of PAL speed (~8312 cycles per tick).<p>Statistics: Posted by <a href="http://forums.nesdev.com/memberlist.php?mode=viewprofile&amp;u=53">Dwedit</a> — Sun Jul 01, 2012 11:31 am</p><hr />
]]></content>
