<id>http://forums.nesdev.com/viewtopic.php?t=9011&amp;p=95523#p95523</id>
<link href="http://forums.nesdev.com/viewtopic.php?t=9011&amp;p=95523#p95523"/>
<title type="html"><![CDATA[APU frame counter speed on Dendy?]]></title>

<content type="html" xml:base="http://forums.nesdev.com/viewtopic.php?t=9011&amp;p=95523#p95523"><![CDATA[
Nintendulator says:<br />constintFrameCyclesNTSC[5] = { 7456,14912,22370,29828,37280 };<br />constintFrameCyclesPAL[5] = { 8312,16626,24938,33252,41560 };<br /><br />But that's not the same as a hardware confirmation.<br /><br />These numbers tell you at what CPU cycle you reach that APU subframe number.  4th number tells you when you get an APU Frame IRQ (in CPU cycles).  5th number only matters if the APU is running in 5 stage mode.<p>Statistics: Posted by <a href="http://forums.nesdev.com/memberlist.php?mode=viewprofile&amp;u=53">Dwedit</a> — Thu Jun 14, 2012 1:47 pm</p><hr />
]]></content>
