<id>http://forums.nesdev.com/viewtopic.php?t=9011&amp;p=95517#p95517</id>
<link href="http://forums.nesdev.com/viewtopic.php?t=9011&amp;p=95517#p95517"/>
<title type="html"><![CDATA[APU frame counter speed on Dendy?]]></title>

<content type="html" xml:base="http://forums.nesdev.com/viewtopic.php?t=9011&amp;p=95517#p95517"><![CDATA[
APU Frame Counter is generated entirely in the CPU. The Dendy CPU runs faster than the PAL NES CPU; the master clock is divided by 15 instead of 16 for compatibility with raster effects in software for the NTSC Famicom.<p>Statistics: Posted by <a href="http://forums.nesdev.com/memberlist.php?mode=viewprofile&amp;u=9">tepples</a> — Thu Jun 14, 2012 10:30 am</p><hr />
]]></content>
